  "issue_title": "[Refactor] use emit_json helper for JSON output in view commands",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nThe `emit_json` helper in `helpers.py` uses `click.echo` for clean machine-readable JSON output\nwithout Rich styling. However, `view.py` bypasses it and uses `console.print(json_mod.dumps(...))`\ndirectly in three commands:\n\n- `issues_list` (lines 86, 88)\n- `issues_pending_harvest` (lines 267-279)\n- `admin_info` (line 314)\n\n`console.print` goes through Rich, which can inject ANSI escape codes or modify output encoding\ndepending on terminal settings. This breaks JSON parsers consuming stdout (e.g. `gitt issues list --json | jq`).\n\nThe miner commands (check.py, post.py) and `emit_error_json` already use `click.echo` for JSON.\nThe view commands should use the existing `emit_json` helper for consistency.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-20T19:39:43.000Z",
